Class CSVBeanRecord

    • Constructor Detail

      • CSVBeanRecord

        public CSVBeanRecord(Object bean)
        Constructs a new CSVBeanRecord that represents the CSV fields indicated by the bean parameter. The lenght of this record is calculated with the sum of the lenght of every field. The value of every field is initialized with a default value (if present)
        Parameters:
        bean - the bean of this CSVBeanRecord

      • CSVBeanRecord

        public CSVBeanRecord(Object bean,
                     String csvRecord)
        Constructs a new CSVBeanRecord that represents the CSV fields indicated by the bean parameter. The lenght of this record is calculated with the sum of the lenght of every field. The value of every field is initialized with the formatted value present in the relative position of the csvRecord parameter
        Parameters:
        bean - the bean of this CSVBeanRecord
        csvRecord - the CSV string of this CSVBeanRecord

      • CSVBeanRecord

        public CSVBeanRecord(Object bean,
                     String csvRecord,
                     List<FieldExtendedProperty> fieldExtendedProperties)
        Constructs a new CSVBeanRecord that represents the CSV fields indicated by the bean parameter. The value of every field is initialized with the formatted value present in the relative position of the csvRecord parameter. To every field of the record are applied the extended properties present in the fieldExtendedProperties parameter. Only the following properties are permitted at record level:
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.LPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.RPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.VALIDATOR
        Parameters:
        bean - the bean of this CSVBeanRecord
        csvRecord - the CSV string of this CSVBeanRecord
        fieldExtendedProperties - the extended properties of field applied to every fields of the record

      • CSVBeanRecord

        public CSVBeanRecord(Object bean,
                     String csvRecord,
                     List<FieldExtendedProperty> fieldExtendedProperties,
                     Map<String,List<FieldExtendedProperty>> mapFieldExtendedProperties)
        Constructs a new CSVBeanRecord that represents the CSV fields indicated by the bean parameter. The value of every field is initialized with the formatted value present in the relative position of the csvRecord parameter. To every field of the record are applied the extended properties present in the fieldExtendedProperties parameter. Only the following properties are permitted at record level:
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.LPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.RPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.VALIDATOR
        The extended property of every field can be overridden with the extended property present in the mapFieldExtendedProperties
        Parameters:
        bean - the bean of this CSVBeanRecord
        csvRecord - the CSV string of this CSVBeanRecord
        fieldExtendedProperties - the extended properties of field applied to every fields of the record
        mapFieldExtendedProperties - the extended properties of fields to override the relative property at record level

      • CSVBeanRecord

        public CSVBeanRecord(Object bean,
                     String csvRecord,
                     List<FieldExtendedProperty> fieldExtendedProperties,
                     Map<String,List<FieldExtendedProperty>> mapFieldExtendedProperties,
                     RecordWay recordWay)
        Constructs a new CSVBeanRecord that represents the CSV fields indicated by the bean parameter. The value of every field is initialized with the formatted value present in the relative position of the csvRecord parameter. To every field of the record are applied the extended properties present in the fieldExtendedProperties parameter. Only the following properties are permitted at record level:
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.LPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.RPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.VALIDATOR
        The extended property of every field can be overridden with the extended property present in the mapFieldExtendedProperties
        Parameters:
        bean - the bean of this CSVBeanRecord
        csvRecord - the formatted string of this CSVBeanRecord
        fieldExtendedProperties - the extended properties of field applied to every fields of the record
        mapFieldExtendedProperties - the extended properties of fields to override the relative property at record level
        recordWay - the record way. This overrides what's defined at annotation level (see FixefidRecord annotation)

      • toString

        public String toString()
                throws RecordException
        Returns a CSV String object representing this record. The returned string is composed with the formatted unpadded value of every field of this record. Every value is separated with the CSVSep defined for this CSV record. If encloseAllFields defined for this CSV record is true, every field of the record is enclosed with the enclosing defined for this CSV record. If the encloseAllFields is false the fields aren't enclosing, eccept they contain the char sep. Each of the embedded char enclosing characters is represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Overrides:
        toString in class AbstractRecord
        Returns:
        a CSV string representation of this record
        Throws:
        RecordException - it the status of this record is ERROR
